<GUIClass name="CMUI_TreeViewForm" id="81845e5c-d96c-4de3-bf12-abaf28a8aed3">
    <superclass name="CM_BaseForm"/>
    <transient/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>
The concept for this form is to provide an interface for editing or viewing
any entity that has child entites (or any number of 'levels' deep). 

Sub-classing and developer information:

*It is likely that you will need to re-implement most of the unprotected methods
*It is possible you may need to re-implement some of the protected methods
*It is unlikely that you will need to re-implement any of the zProtected methods

See GTE_ReleaseRequests sub-class as an example pf how to re-implement.

In edit mode, the form only keeps a reference to the master proxy entity. 
You are expected to add and accociate child proxy objects with the master proxy
as the user adds them.

In edit mode, as the user clicks on different objects in the tree, proxy objects
need to be updated with any entry changes as the user clicks around.
If the user is in edit mode and clicks on a different entity in the tree, 
the self.saveUserEntry method stub is called (self.mySelectedObject is 
still the previous object at this point) followed by the self.doTreeClick method 
stub (in which self.mySelectedObject is now the newly selected object).
You can then use the same entry table for each object and re-populate it 
with relivant fields for the object type.
</text>
